ive in the minds of later generations. I am thinking of aurochs and angels, the secret of durable pigments, prophetic sonnets, the refuge of art. And this is the only immortality you and I may share, my Lolita.





Vladimir Nabokov

ON A BOOK ENTITLED LOLITA



